* Target audience

  This document is intended for no.bbs.trust maintenance personnel

* Document responsible

  The component responsible is responsible for this document.

Installation/Deployment

* General

  ts_idp_nemid-war is probably the most important component in the whole it universe...

* Environment

  The production environment specification for this module and how it correlates to the other COI modules are defined in the site specification [SSPEC]

* Start/Stop

** Stop the ts_idp_nemid application

  * Open a terminal to the target local zone
  
  * # /opt/sun_web/servers/https-ts_idp_nemid/bin/stopserv 

** Start the ts_idp_nemid application

  * Open a terminal to the target local zone
  
  * # /opt/sun_web/servers/https-ts_idp_nemid/bin/startserv
  
* Parameters

  All parameters used for the ts_idp_nemid application to start and function correctly are contained in the following files. 
  Properties that should be set default to a specific value are not in cursive. 
  Properties that are not static and might be changed are in cursive.

  * {rootArtifactId}.properties
  
    * key=value
  
  * secrets.properties

    * key=value

  * log4j.properties

    * key=value
  
Logging

* General

  For logging the application uses log4j.

* Logfiles

The logfiles for the ts_idp_nemid application are

  * ts_idp_nemid.log
  
  * ts_idp_nemid-trapometer.log
  
  * ts_idp_nemid-dosometer.log 
  
  * ts_idp_nemid-branchometer.log
  

* Changing log level

  To change the loglevel for ts_idp_nemid.log do the following:

  * Open the log4j.properties file
  
  * Choose wanted loglevel
  
  * Restart application

* Error codes

** Error 1 codes

*-------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
|<<ErrCode 1>>      |<<Description>>                                              |
*-------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
|D100               |Do nothing at the time, just report the error                |
*-------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
|D110               |Restart component                                            |
*-------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
|D120               |Check if the database process is running                     |
*-------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
|D130               |Call maintenance personell                                   |
*-------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+

** Error 2 codes

*-------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
|<<ErrCode 2>>      |<<Description>>                                              |
*-------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
|1401               |Something went wrong                                         |
*-------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+
|...                |...                                                          |
*-------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------+

